fix: mobile nav hidden on desktop - remove inline display:flex override

Root cause: the nav element in MobileNav.tsx had an inline style
  { display: 'flex' }
which always overrides CSS class rules, including media queries.
The CSS class had display:none for screens >= 768px but the inline
style was winning, so the mobile nav bar appeared on desktop too.

Fix:
- Removed display:'flex' from the inline style in MobileNav.tsx
  so the .mobile-nav CSS class fully controls visibility
- Added display:none !important in globals.css for screens >= 768px
  as a safety guard against future inline style conflicts
